# SEO, AEO, GEO, and Google Search Console (2026)

Companion to **`best-practices-2026.mdc`**. Detailed file-specific rules stay in scoped **`.mdc`** files (metadata, sitemap, robots, JSON-LD, page marketing)—this file orients agents on **search**, **answers**, **entities**, and **GSC**.

## SEO (traditional search)

- **`metadataBase`**, canonical, and **`alternates`** — follow **`lib-seo-metadata.mdc`** for `**/lib/metadata*.ts` and page-level metadata.
- **Unique** title, meta description, and **one H1** per route — **`real-estate-page-marketing.mdc`** for `**/app/**/page.tsx`.
- **Internal links** with descriptive anchor text; align visible **NAP** with GBP and JSON-LD.
- **Sitemap** absolute URLs, same origin as production — **`app-sitemap-metadata.mdc`** (`**/sitemap.ts`).
- **Robots**: allow marketing HTML; avoid blocking `/_next/static` CSS/JS needed for rendering — **`app-robots-metadata.mdc`** (`**/robots.ts`).
- **Structured data**: extend existing generators; avoid conflicting duplicate graphs — **`real-estate-jsonld-schema.mdc`**, **`seo-structured-data-components.mdc`**.

## AEO (answer engine optimization)

- Use **question-shaped headings** (H2/H3) where they match real user queries; **answer in the first paragraph** under each heading when appropriate.
- **FAQ sections**: pair visible Q&A with valid **`FAQPage`** / **`Question`** + **`Answer`** JSON-LD when content is static and accurate — see **`real-estate-jsonld-schema.mdc`**.
- Avoid **thin or duplicate** FAQ blocks that repeat the same answer across many URLs without local differentiation.

## GEO (generative / entity optimization)

- **Stable entities**: one canonical business name, phone, and address; reuse **`@id`** and **`url`** in JSON-LD consistently with visible copy and **`lib-site-contact.mdc`**.
- Prefer **first-party, citable** facts (service area, license, brokerage); align with **content integrity** in **`best-practices-2026.mdc`** (no fabricated review counts, rankings, or volume).

## Google Search Console

- **Property host**: match how the site is served (e.g. `https://www.example.com` vs apex); keep **Search Console**, **sitemap**, **robots `Sitemap:`**, and **`metadataBase`** on the same canonical host.
- **URL Inspection**: use for a **single URL** (live vs Google, fetch status, indexing). **Request indexing** sparingly for high-priority pages.
- **Page indexing** reports:
  - **Page with redirect** for `http://`, apex, or non-canonical `www` variants is often **expected** when the canonical URL is elsewhere; validate the **destination** URL is indexed.
  - **Discovered – currently not indexed** often reflects **crawl queue / priority**, not necessarily a code bug—confirm sitemap, no `noindex`, and 200 responses for important URLs.
  - **Blocked by robots.txt** for `/_next/static/...` assets: remove blanket **`Disallow: /_next/`** if present so crawlers can fetch static chunks.
- **Enhancements** (e.g. Review snippets): fix invalid JSON-LD (e.g. integer **`reviewCount`**, valid parent types, **`itemReviewed`** on **`Review`**); validate with [Rich Results Test](https://search.google.com/test/rich-results).
- After deploy, allow **days to weeks** for reports to reflect fixes.

## What this rule does not replace

- **GBP-style posts, video scripts, and long-form marketing copy** (voice, local specificity, anti-template rules) — use **`content.mdc`** when those files match its globs.
- Full NAP tables, GBP field-by-field copy, or every **`page.tsx`** checklist — use **`real-estate-page-marketing.mdc`** and **`lib-site-contact.mdc`**.
- CSP, RealScout, middleware — **`best-practices-2026.mdc`**, **`middleware-security.mdc`**, **`next-config-headers.mdc`**.
